#: ../../M/Mars.rst:5
msgid "Mars"
msgstr "Mars"

#: ../../M/Mars.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../M/Mars.rst:9
msgid ""
"A legendary tragic failure, the archetypal Hacker Dream Gone Wrong. Mars was"
" the code name for a family of PDP-10-compatible computers built by Systems "
"Concepts (now, The SC Group): the multi-processor SC-30M, the small "
"uniprocessor SC-25, and the never-built superprocessor SC-40. These machines"
" were marvels of engineering design; although not much slower than the "
"unique :ref:`Foonly` F-1, they were physically smaller and consumed less "
"power than the much slower :ref:`DEC` KS10 or Foonly F-2, F-3, or F-4 "
"machines. They were also completely compatible with the DEC KL10, and ran "
"all KL10 binaries (including the operating system) with no modifications at "
"about 2--3 times faster than a KL10."
msgstr ""
"伝説的な悲劇の失敗、ハッカーの夢が間違った方向に進んだ典型例。Marsは、Systems Concepts(現在はThe SC "
"Group)が製造したPDP-10互換コンピュータ一族のコードネームだった。マルチプロセッサのSC-30M、小型のユニプロセッサSC-25、そして決して製造されなかった超プロセッサSC-40である。これらの機械は工学設計の驚異だった。唯一無二の\\"
" :ref:`Foonly`\\ F-1よりさほど遅くないにもかかわらず、物理的により小さく、はるかに遅い\\ :ref:`DEC`\\ "
"KS10やFoonly F-2、F-3、F-4の機械より消費電力が少なかった。それらはまたDEC "
"KL10と完全に互換性があり、すべてのKL10バイナリ(オペレーティングシステムを含む)を無改造で、KL10の約2〜3倍速く実行した。"

#: ../../M/Mars.rst:14
msgid ""
"When DEC cancelled the Jupiter project in 1983 (their followup to the "
"PDP-10), Systems Concepts should have made a bundle selling their machine "
"into shops with a lot of software investment in PDP-10s, and in fact their "
"spring 1984 announcement generated a great deal of excitement in the PDP-10 "
"world. TOPS-10 was running on the Mars by the summer of 1984, and TOPS-20 by"
" early fall. Unfortunately, the hackers running Systems Concepts were much "
"better at designing machines than at mass producing or selling them; the "
"company allowed itself to be sidetracked by a bout of perfectionism into "
"continually improving the design, and lost credibility as delivery dates "
"continued to slip. They also overpriced the product ridiculously; they "
"believed they were competing with the KL10 and :ref:`VAX` 8600 and failed to"
" reckon with the likes of Sun Microsystems and other hungry startups "
"building workstations with power comparable to the KL10 at a fraction of the"
" price. By the time SC shipped the first SC-30M to Stanford in late 1985, "
"most customers had already made the traumatic decision to abandon the "
"PDP-10, usually for VMS or Unix boxes. Most of the Mars computers built "
"ended up being purchased by CompuServe."
msgstr ""
"DECが1983年にJupiterプロジェクト(PDP-10の後継)を中止したとき、Systems "
"ConceptsはPDP-10に多額のソフトウェア投資をした店舗に自社の機械を売って大儲けできたはずであり、実際1984年春の発表はPDP-10の世界で大きな興奮を生んだ。1984年の夏までにMars上でTOPS-10が、初秋までにTOPS-20が動いた。残念ながら、Systems"
" "
"Conceptsを運営していたハッカーたちは、機械を大量生産したり売ったりするよりも設計するほうがはるかに得意だった。会社は完璧主義の発作にそれて設計を絶えず改良し続け、納期が遅れ続けて信用を失った。彼らはまた製品にとんでもなく高い値段をつけた。自分たちはKL10や\\"
" :ref:`VAX`\\ 8600と競争していると信じ、KL10に匹敵する性能のワークステーションをその何分の一かの価格で作るSun "
"Microsystemsやその他の飢えた新興企業の類を計算に入れなかった。SCが1985年後半に最初のSC-30MをStanfordに出荷するころには、ほとんどの顧客はすでにPDP-10を捨てるという痛ましい決断をし、たいていVMSやUnixの機械に乗り換えていた。製造されたMarsコンピュータのほとんどは結局CompuServeに購入された。"

#: ../../M/Mars.rst:21
msgid ""
"This tale and the related saga of :ref:`Foonly` hold a lesson for hackers: "
"if you want to play in the :ref:`Real-World`\\, you need to learn Real World"
" moves."
msgstr ""
"この物語と\\ :ref:`Foonly`\\ の関連する物語はハッカーへの教訓を含んでいる。\\ :ref:`Real-World`\\ "
"で遊びたいなら、現実世界の手口を学ぶ必要がある、と。"
